16 WHEREAS, Judge Veal has further demonstrated a steadfast commitment to reform and
17 rehabilitation through her oversight of the Henry County Adult Felony Drug Court Program,
18 championing initiatives that provide opportunities for drug offenders to reintegrate into
19 society and pursue paths to recovery; and
20 WHEREAS, outside the courtroom, she remains deeply engaged in her community and
21 serves on the Board of Directors for the Hands of Hope Clinic; and
22 WHEREAS, as additional testament to her excellent service, she was previously honored by
23 the Georgia Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers for her leadership as chair of the
24 Debra Blum Mental Health Committee; and
25 WHEREAS, with her steadfast dedication to justice and the proper administration of the law,
26 Judge Holly W. Veal continues to inspire and lead, and it is abundantly fitting and proper that
27 she be appropriately honored.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body recognize and commend Judge Holly W. Veal for her efficient,
30 effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of Georgia and extend their
31 most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Judge
34 Holly W. Veal.
